        <projectContents><![CDATA[<div id="post-1889" class="post">
<div>
<p>mogrify<span> </span>(like<span> </span>convert) is one of the utilities that come with<span> </span><a href="http://www.imagemagick.org/">imagemagick</a>.</p>
<p>Here's an example of how you convert a batch of<span> </span>pic<span> </span>files to<span> </span>jpeg. Same for png to jpeg, vice-versa, etc.</p>
<pre>$ mogrify -format jpg *.pic</pre>
<p>Boom! Next!</p>
<p>Also see:<span> </span><a href="http://www.phpied.com/ffmpeg-batch-convert/">batch convert audio/video files with ffmpeg</a></p>
